The paper discusses a testing framework for constraint programming, which involves refining a declarative model using classical techniques and thoroughly testing the improved model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category, as constraint programming is a subfield of AI. Additionally, the paper discusses software engineering practices and testing, which could place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The use of techniques such as constraint reformulation and symmetry-breaking suggests that the paper could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a general framework for constraint program development, which could place it in the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category.
